  "en_notes_asad": [
    {
      "note_no": "1",
      "note": "Since what is termed \"death\" is stated here to have been created, it cannot be identical with \"non-existence\", but obviously must have a positive reality of its own. To my mind, it connotes, firstly, the inanimate state of existence preceding the emergence of life in plants or animated beings; and, secondly, the state of transition from life as we know it in this world to the - as yet to us unimaginable - condition off existence referred to in the Qur'an as \"the hereafter\" or \"the life to come\" (al-akhirah)."
    }
